      </p>

      <h2 id="account-deletion-and-data-removal">9. Account Deletion and Data Removal</h2>

      <h3>9.1 Your Right to Delete</h3>
      <p>
        You may delete your account at any time through Settings. Upon
        deletion:
      </p>
      <p>
        <strong>Your activity data:</strong> Your user record, all attendance records,
        contribution records, and peer attestations are permanently deleted.
      </p>
      <p>
        <strong>Your identity link:</strong> The connection between your identity and your
        blockchain wallet address is permanently severed. Your wallet becomes
        an anonymous, unlinked address.
      </p>
      <p>
        <strong>On-chain records:</strong> Attestations, token balances, and staking positions
        on the public blockchain cannot be deleted. However, without the
        identity link (which has been deleted), these records cannot be linked
        back to you.
      </p>

      <h3>9.2 Irreversibility</h3>
      <p>
        Account deletion is permanent and cannot be undone. We cannot recover
